[Andreas] Create the enum representation of the maze blocks
Each character represents a building block for the maze. Will enums to represent them internally because I like enums better than constant characters and strings.

[Andreas] Read a file to create a maze and will count walls and spaces
The maze explorer must be passed the name fo the file that will build the maze. This will make it more versatile in the future and also helps making the tests more independent from the actual implementation details (resources in test).
[Andreas] Tell what kind of block is in the specific coordinates

[Andreas] Change game to load all mazes in a resources
Maze files are now located under the mazes/ directory in resources. The game will now read all files and load them in its memory.
